It's uncanny how often posts with &quot;All you need&quot; in the title outperform the substance underneath.<p>It all started with the famous &quot;Attention is all you need&quot; paper. In the meantime, people have come up with<p>&quot;Spreadsheets are all you need&quot;
&quot;Claude Code is all you need&quot;
&quot;Cheating is All You Need&quot;
&quot;Tools: Code Is All You Need&quot;
&quot;Text Is All You Need&quot;<p>People see it and immediately assume someone has boiled down a universe of complexity into one neat takeaway - no matter how vacuous the content is.<p>This post is here to prove the point. It has no real secret. The secret is the title. And if you're reading this far, the experiment already worked.

